Name :- Work Opportunities in Japan

Technologies Used :- HTML, CSS, vanilla Javascript

Description :-Creating a complete, responsive job portal website using HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript involves several components. Here's a basic structure and description for each section:

1.Header Section:
Include the logo or website name.
Navigation menu with links to different sections like Home, Jobs, About, Contact, etc.

2.Job Listings Section:
Display job listings with brief information like job title, company, location, and a short description.
Include pagination or infinite scroll for navigating through multiple job listings.

3.Filter Section:
Allow users to filter job listings based on criteria such as job type, location, salary range, etc.

Job Details Section:
When a user clicks on a job listing, display detailed information about the job on the separate page.
